====Usage notes====
* ''Was'' is colloquially used with prepositions, chiefly but not exclusively in southern regions. Otherwise it is generally replaced with a pronominal adverb containing {{m|de|wo-}} (or in a few cases {{m|de|wes-}}). Hence: {{l|de||'''''Womit''' hast du das gemacht?''|With what did you do that?}}, instead of '''''Mit was''' hast du das gemacht?'', and {{m|de|weswegen}} instead of ''wegen was''.
* The genitive case, and the dative case if necessary for clearness, can be paraphrased by means of {{m|de|[[welcher]] [[Sache]]||what thing}}. [[possessive|Possessive]] genitives are more commonly paraphrased with {{m|de|wovon||of what}}.
* The colloquial ''was'' meaning "something" can only be the first word in a sentence if followed by an adjective: {{l|de||''Was Wichtiges fehlt noch.''|Something important is missing.}} Otherwise the full form ''etwas'' must be used: {{l|de||''Etwas fehlt noch.''|Something is missing.}} The reason for this is that the latter sentence could be misinterpreted as a question if ''was'' were used.

